$interpreted: Narrator: It is said that a long, long time ago......
Narrator: There was once a band of robbers who stooped to no end of evil, looting and pillaging...
Narrator: Despite the troops' best efforts to capture them, there was a beautiful woman among the robbers who stirred up and encouraged her accomplices with her charm and grace.
Narrator: In the face of this rampant malevolence and the withering away of justice and righteousness—
Chiyuki: Stop!
Fierce Robber: Who are you!?
Chiyuki: The White Plume.
Narrator: That's right! The very incarnation of beauty and justice~~
Narrator: Our gorgeous heroine, the White Plume.
Fierce Robber: That ain't possible! What's the White Plume doing here!?
Ravishing Woman: Who cares who she is, let's hurry up and get her dealt with!
Ravishing Woman: [Windmoon Dance]!
Chiyuki: So, you're using your beauty to cajole your cronies, are you?
Chiyuki: Let's see just how powerful this little madam really is.
Chiyuki: Exquisite flowers reflected in pure snows—fear melts away, and courage sweeps forth... [Snowdrop Reflection]!
Stunned Guard: Wow!!! She's beaming with power! Incredible!
Ravishing Woman: Hey! What are you all looking at? Face me!
Chiyuki: Come on, boys. Let's book these no-good evildoers.
Ravishing Woman: Dammit... I can't believe my charms have been defeated...
Chiyuki: If you come for the queen, you best not miss.
Narrator: That's a wrap! Awesome job!
Chiyuki: Well done, everyone.
Actor Playing Guard: Great work, Miss Chiyuki~
Director: That was perfect, Chiyuki! You've got it down just right! Good heavens, we've got a true star in our midsts~
Director: "The White Plume" is practically guaranteed to be a smash hit when we open! I just know it!
Chiyuki: Please, you flatter me. It's an honor to be part of this play.
Director: Oh no, you mustn't be so modest, darling. You'll be Alliance Beauty before you know it.
Actor Playing Ravishing Woman: Yeah, right. Don't you think there's something odd about this play?
Chiyuki: (Am I still not good enough for you?)
Director: What do you mean? What's odd about it?
Actor Playing Robber: Yeah... Maybe it's the script...
Director: You're telling me there's something wrong with my script!?
Director: I wrote this play especially for Chiyuki! What would a C-lister like you know about it!
Actor Playing Ravishing Woman: There's definitely some problems with it, just look at this part...
Chiyuki: (It's not a problem with the script. The story's all about the power of beauty, but...)
Actor Playing Robber: Honestly, the whole fighting-with-beauty thing is totally ridiculous. It's... how can I say this... unconvincing.
Chiyuki: (Unconvincing!)
Actor Playing Ravishing Woman: And vacuous.
Chiyuki: (Vacuous!)
Director: What are you trying to say, that there's no life in this!?
Chiyuki: (No... life...)
Chiyuki: (Yeah. That's the problem with the lead actress.)
Chiyuki: (I haven't let any beauty shine through. I'll never be able to win the audience over.)
Chiyuki: (And forget about... being Alliance Beauty...)
Chiyuki: (I've dieted, got into shape, tried mud baths and spa treatments, the works... but it's not enough. It'll never be enough...)
Chiyuki: (I'm a withering old maid... That's my fate...)
Actor Playing Ravishing Woman: Hey, we'd surely do a better job showing off our beauty if we could get the legendary Last Orchid to direct us.
Chiyuki: The legendary who?
Actor Playing Ravishing Woman: Ehh!? You mean you don't know, Chiyuki?

Actor Playing Ravishing Woman: They say this great master devoted his entire life to the pursuit of flawless beauty. If we could get just a few tips from him we'd surely be able to take this to the next level.
Chiyuki: (What on earth is she on about... Is she serious?)
Director: It's just a rumor, my darling, a rumor.
Actor Playing Robber: But it's a right real-sounding rumor.
Chiyuki: So... Do they also say where we can find him?
Director: Are you interested too, Chiyuki?
Chiyuki: Uh... no, I just like hearing tall tales.
Director: Right you are. Miss Chiyuki's a goddess already, we don't need to hear such absurd nonsense.
Chiyuki: Don't say that. Just think of it as more inspiration.
Chiyuki: So where do the legends say we can find him?
Actor Playing Ravishing Woman: Hmm, let's see... They say he lives deep in the Infinite Peaks.
Chiyuki: (The Infinite Peaks... That can't be too far, right? I'll just pack an overnight bag and...)
Chiyuki: I have something I must attend to. I'll take my leave of you now, if that's all right.
Director: Of course. Let's wrap up here, everybody.
Chiyuki: ....This is harder than I thought it'd be...
Wild Beast: Grrr~~
Chiyuki: Uhh... Nice doggy... I'm just passing by... I won't hurt you...
Chiyuki: No!
Chiyuki: Finally... got away...
Chiyuki: Oh no! Where am I...? Wasn't I just here earlier...?
Chiyuki: ...How'd I get back here... This can't be right...
Chiyuki: Master Orchid... where are you...
Chiyuki: Uh...
Chiyuki: Where am I...?
???: The Infinite Peaks.
Chiyuki: Who are you!?
???: I've... long forgotten my name...
Chiyuki: What!?
???: Travel beyond the ends of the earth, roam further than the edge of heaven...
Chiyuki: ……！
???: Even when time's shrivelled up, the myriad flowers still remain.
Chiyuki: Could it be? Are you...
Master Orchid: They call me—the Last Orchid.
